               <head>Rumi’s Masnavi, books I, V-VI; splendid copy</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Mas̲navī-'i maʿnavī by Rūmī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1104E-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176928.0x000001 viaf_98930150">Rūmī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="viaf_98930150">رومى </persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20506">Mas̲navī-'i maʿnavī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_20506">مثنوى معنوى</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Incomplete volume of a once splendidly transcribed copy of daftars I, V-VI of the <title>Mas̲navī-'i maʿnavī</title> by <persName key="viaf_98930150" role="aut">Rūmī</persName>
                           <persName key="viaf_98930150" role="aut">Mawlānā Jalāl al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn Muḥammad Bahāʾ al-Dīn Valad Balkhī</persName> (d. 670/1271). 
                        </p>
                        <p>It is clear from discrepancies in the original Persian foliation that substantial portions of this volume were missing before the addition of stamped foliation in the IOL. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 154v): completed Friday, 22 Z̲ī al-Ḥijjah 1007/16 July 1599. </p>
                        <p>Illuminated frontispieces at the beginning of each daftar (ff. 1v-2r, 24v, 87v), neat gold, black, and blue rulings throughout. 
</p>
                        <p>Excellent calligraphic nastaʿlīq-i khafī throughout. 
</p>
                        <p>Annotations and corrections in margins and interlinear spaces throughout. 
</p>
                        <p>Stamped and Persian foliation. 
</p>
                        <p>Lacking original binding. Detached and damaged leather binding (blind tooled medallions with painted rulings on dark brown leather; reddish brown leather doublures); delaminated; wormholes. 
</p>
                        <p>Folios unbound; cropped, wormholes, creased, water and fungal stains, later repairs. </p>
                        <p>Substantial areas of text lost in parts. 
</p>
                        <p>Ownership marks and possible seal impressions erased at beginning. 
</p>
                        <p>Condition extremely fragile. </p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
